Let's make High Protein, Instant viral bun dosa.A single bun dosa gives nearly 8.5gm proteins.

Bun dosa

Serving-6

Ingredients

1-Sooji-1 cup(120gm)

2-Curd-1 cup(250gm)

3-Onion-50gm

4-Green chili-as per taste

5-Carrot-50gm

6-Paneer-120gm

7-Dhaniya-as per taste

8-Salt-as per taste

9-Oil-20ml

10-Ajanta baking soda-1/4th tsp

Method

1-In a bowl add sooji, curd and 1/2 cup water mix well.

2-Keep it aside for 20 mins, now add it in mixer jar and grind it as fine paste.

3-Add chopped onion, chili, carrot, paneer, dhaniya , salt and mix well.

4-Now add baking soda and mix well.

5-Heat a tadka pan add few drops oil pour the mixture on tadka pan and cook both sides.

6-Healthy and tasty high protein bun dosa is ready to serve.

Let's Make No Rice, Gluten free, High protein Dosa. A Single Dosa gives 102 calories and 7gm proteins. 

Protein dosa

Serving-10-12dosa

Ingredients

1-Urad dal-1/2cup

2-Soyabean-1/2cup

3-Chana Dal-1/4th cup

4-Oats-1cup

5-Methi seeds-1tsp

Method

1-In a bowl add urad dal, soyabean, chana dal, oats, methi and wash it 2-3times.

2-Now add water and soak it for 6 hours. 

3-Now Grind it as fine paste. 

4-Mix well and keep it aside overnight for fermentation. 

5-Spread it on tawa and cook both sides. 

6-Healthy protein dosa is ready to serve.

No Sugar,No Oil,No egg,No Oven Healthy high Protein Mug Cake.This is super healthy and easy to prepare.A single mug cake gives nearly 34gm proteins.To make this recipe I am using few ingredients and for proteins I add @qnt.india Prime whey protein powder.

Single scoop of protein powder gives 25gm protein and 122 calories.It doesn't contain any added sugar,and super delicious.

You can check their products from their website, use my code -Qntsmriti for extra 7%discount.

High Protein Mug Cake

Ingredients 

1-Oats Powder-20gm

2-Protein powder-1 scoop

3-Milk-100ml

4-Peanut butter-10gm

5-Chopped nuts-1tsp

6-Sugat free dark chocolate -Optional

7-Baking soada-1/4th tsp

Method

1-In a mug add oats powder,Qnt prime whey powder, peanut butter,milk and mix well.

2-Now add baking soda and mix well.

3-At last add chopped nuts and dark chocolate.

4-Steam it for 20mins on gas.

5-Healthy High Protein Mug cake is ready to serve.

Let’s make sugar Free Lauki ka halwa.This is super healthy and easy to prepare.A single serving of Lauki halwa gives 169 calories and 4.95gm protein.To make this recipe I am using Lauki, dates, milk and @Aashirvaad 90% Lower Cholesterol Ghee This ghee has 90% less cholesterol than traditional ghee. The cholesterol is removed using Advanced Cholesterol - Lowering Adsorption Process. Made from quality-tested cow milk butter, this ghee is slow cooked for 3.5 hours, ensuring the great taste and rich aroma as a regular ghee. 

You can purchase from-https://www.aashirvaadsvasti.in/our-product/aashirvaad-svasti-90-lower-cholesterol-cow-ghee.html

Lauki Halwa

Serving-5

1-Lauki-400gm

2-Milk-500ml

3-Dates-60gm

4-Cashew nuts-30gm

5-Kesar-6-7 stands

6-Aashirwad 90% Lower cholesterol ghee-10gm

Method

1-In a bowl add deseeded dates, Cashew nuts , kesar and milk, soak it for 1 hour.

2-Now grind it as fine paste.

3-Take a Medium size lauki, wash, peel and grate it.

4-In a pan add ghee, add grated lauki and fry it for 10 mins, in medium flame.

5-Now add milk and cook for 5-6mins.

6-Add dates paste and cook it for 5-6 mins.

7-Serve hot and garnish with chopped nuts.

8-Super healthy sugar free lauki halwa is ready to serve.

Nutrition Information

Single serving halwa

Calories-168kcal

Protein-4.95gm

Carb-15.97

Fibre-2.71

*Traditional Ghee refers to Aashirvaad Svasti Pure Cow Ghee

Method

2-In a bowl add chopped onion, chopped capsicum, boiled corn, grated carrot, grated paneer, coriander leaves, chopped green chili, crushed garlic, spices and salt, mix well.

3-Now add water and mix well.

4-Grease the appe pan add this mixer to appe pan and cook well.

Let’s make Indian street food , but with a twist. This is low calorie makhana chaat best alternative of potato chaat, super healthy and easy to prepare.A single serving makhana chaat gives  267 calories and nearly 14.4gm proteins and12.63gm fibre.

Diet Makhana Chaat

Serves:2

Ingredients:

Drypeas-120gm 

Foxnut-30gm

Onion-80gm

Tomato-100gm

Chili-as per taste

Turmeric powder-1/2tsp

Red chili powder-1/2tsp

Salt-as per taste

Mint coriander chutney-as per taste 

Coriander leaves- 2 tbsp

Ghee-2.5gm

Tamarind juice-5 spoon

Procedure:

In pressure cooker add soaked dry peas,water, chopped onion, tomato, chili and turmeric

powder,salt,cook it until 5whistles came. 

Once peas cooked add tamarind juice, coriander leaves, mix well.

In a pan add ghee,turmeric powder,coriander powder, red chili powder, salt and little water, now add roasted foxnut, fry for 2 mins.

In a bowl add ragda, finely chopped onion, tomato,mint coriander chutney,masala makhana and garnish with coriander leaves.

Serve Immediately.
